question:
The lines $y = -2x + 8$ and $y = \frac{1}{2} x - 2$ meet at $(4,0),$ as shown. What is the area of the triangle formed by these two lines and the line $x = -2?$ [asy]
draw((-8,0)--(15,0),black+linewidth(1));
draw((-8,0)--(15,0),EndArrow);
draw((0,-8)--(0,15),black+linewidth(1));
draw((0,-8)--(0,15),EndArrow);
draw((-2,-9)--(-2,16),black+linewidth(1));
draw((-3.5,15)--(8,-8),black+linewidth(1));
draw((-8,-6)--(8,2),black+linewidth(1));
label("$y$",(0,15),N);
label("$x$",(15,0),E);
label("$x=-2$",(-2,-9),S);
label("$(4,0)$",(3,-2),S);
label("$y=\frac{1}{2}x-2$",(8,2),NE);
label("$y=-2x+8$",(8,-8),SE);
[/asy]

What is the area in square units of the quadrilateral XYZW shown below? [asy]
size(200); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
pair X = (0,0), Y = 96*dir(45), Z = (Y.x + 32, Y.y), W = (Z.x,Z.y - 24);
draw(X--Y--Z--W--cycle);
draw(rightanglemark(Y,Z,W,100));
label("$X$",X,SW); label("$Y$",Y,NW); label("$Z$",Z,NE); label("$W$",W,SE); label("96",X--Y,NW); label("104",X--W,SE); label("24",Z--W,E); label("32",Y--Z,N);
[/asy]

The figure below is composed of the rectangles $A$, $B$, $C$, and $D$ with whole number values for length and width. The areas of regions $A$, $B$, and $C$ in square meters, are shown in the diagram. What is the area in square meters of rectangle $D$? [asy]
draw((0,0)--(0,11)--(13,11)--(13,0)--cycle);
draw((0,6)--(13,6)); draw((8,11)--(8,0));
label("$A$",(0,11),SE); label("$B$",(8,11),SE); label("$C$",(8,6),SE); label("$D$",(0,6),SE);
label("40",(6,9)); label("25",(11,9)); label("30",(11,2)); label("?", (6,2));
[/asy]

In the figure shown, $AC=13$ and $DC=2$ units.  What is the length of the segment $BD$? Express your answer in simplest radical form.

[asy]
draw((0,5)--(12,5));
draw((12,5)--(12,0));
draw((12,0)--(0,5));
draw((12,5)--(10.1,0.8));
draw((10.48,1.64)--(9.47,2.06));
draw((9.47,2.06)--(9.09,1.22));
draw((11,5)--(11,4));
draw((11,4)--(12,4));
